04879nam a22008055i 9783110924800DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20112000gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109248007 a10.1515/97831109248002doi  a(DE-B1597)45633  a(OCoLC)979629044  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aP281b.P678 2000eb 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a41522200aProbleme der Interaktion von Lexik und Aspekt (ILA) /chrsg. von Walter Breu.  aReprint 2012 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2011] 4c©2000  a1 online resource (246 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLinguistische Arbeiten ,x0344-6727 ;v4120 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer Sammelband befaßt sich mit dem Einfluß der lexikalischen Bedeutung auf die Funktionen des Verbalaspekts. Grammatischer Aspekt und aspektsensitive Verbklassen (Aktionsarten), die auf den Grenzeigenschaften bzw. Phasenstrukturen von Sachverhalten beruhen, werden dabei systematisch getrennt. Bei den untersuchten Aspektkategorien liegen Schwerpunkte auf der Opposition "perfektiv : imperfektiv" (einschließlich Aorist, Imperfekt, Prozessiv) und auf dem "Perfekt". Daneben werden "Proximativ" und "Ingressiv" sowie die Frage der Relevanz aspektsensitiver Verbklassen auch für (aktionale) Verbalperiphrasen behandelt. Die Daten stammen aus Sprachen sehr verschiedener Gruppen und Typen.  aThis collection examines the influence of lexical meaning on the functions of verb aspect. A systematic distinction is made between grammatical aspect and aspect-sensitive verb-classes (Aktionsarten) defined in terms of the boundary features or phase structures of what they refer to. Among the aspect categories discussed, emphasis is given to the completive/non-perfective opposition (including aorist, imperfect, progressive) and the 'perfect' form. In addition there is discussion of the 'proximative' and the 'ingressive' and the question of the relevance of aspect-sensitive verb-classes for (actional) verb periphrases. The data are taken from languages of very different groups and types.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxAspectvCongresses. 0aLexicologyvCongresses. 4aAspekt ‹Linguistik›. 4aKongress. 4aKonstanz ‹1995›. 4aWortschatz. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBickel, Balthasar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreu, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreu, Walter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChapado Chorro, Μ. Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCsató, Éva Ágnes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrolc, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardenghi, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohanson, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeluda-Voß, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMosel, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSasse, Hans-Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS0 cprintz978348430412340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092480040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110924800423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110924800/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aG